- Use **matplotlib** with sans-serif font family `Arial` (10–12 pt) and black text. Title case, italicised figure titles beneath the figure number.:contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}
- Axis labels sentence-case; only initial capitals for proper nouns.
- Apply **color-blind-safe palettes** (e.g., `mpl.cycler` with blue-orange-green); ensure ≥ 3:1 contrast.:contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}
- Restrict gridlines to subtle gray (#d9d9d9) dashed lines; remove chartjunk.
- Single-column figures: width 5–8.4 cm; two-column: 10.6–17.5 cm; height never exceeds page margins.:contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}
- Add succinct **“Note.”** below figure where clarifications, abbreviations, or copyright statements are needed.:contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}
- Save vector graphics as `PDF` (preferred) or high-res `PNG` (≥ 600 dpi).
- Use descriptive, snake-case filenames (`fig_stroop_rt_by_condition.pdf`).
- Embed code snippet for consistent style: `plt.rcParams.update({...})` (see `@mpl_apa_style.py` for full template).
